main event: A bright white light was observed in the sky over the ocean at 35.53N 164.15E on January 25, 1964.
interesting points: The light was described as being as bright as a first magnitude star.
The light was believed to be a satellite based on its brightness and movement.
The weather was reported as sea calm with scattered clouds and unlimited visibility.
The light was observed at an elevation of 30 degrees and on a course of 170 degrees.
The duration of the sighting was not provided.
